[According to the most recent WHO global update, seasonal influenza activity has continued to increase in the northern hemisphere with influenza A(H3N2) viruses predominating so far (http://www.who.int/influenza/surveillance_monitoring/updates/latest_update_GIP_surveillance/en/). The antigenic characterization of the most recent A(H3N2) viruses so far indicated differences from the A(H3N2) virus used in the influenza vaccines for the northern hemisphere 2014-2015, and likely enhanced severity of the 2014/15 seasonal outbreak. The report from Michigan may be the 1st confirmation of this prediction. - Mod.CP

The state of Michigan can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3057658,22500. Jackson County in south central Michigan can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/michigan-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
